{"title_page": "Y\u016bko Mizutani", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Y\u016bko Mizutani\n| image              = YukoMizutani.jpg\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software  -->\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u6c34\u8c37\u512a\u5b50\n| native_name_lang   = ja\n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name --> \n| birth_date         = {{birth date|1964|11|04}}\n| birth_place        = [[Ama District, Aichi]], Japan\n| death_date         = {{Death date and age|2016|05|17|1964|11|04}}\n| death_place        = [[Tokyo]], Japan \n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n*Actress\n*[[Voice acting in Japan|voice actress]]\n*narrator\n*singer\n}}\n| years_active       = 1985&ndash;2016\n| agent              = [[Aoni Production]]\n| height             = 157 cm\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Mizuho Nishikubo|November 1994|May 17, 2016}}\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Y\u016bko Mizutani'''|\u6c34\u8c37 \u512a\u5b50|Mizutani Y\u016bko|November 4, 1964 \u2013 May 17, 2016}} was a Japanese actress, [[Voice acting in Japan|voice actress]], narrator and singer from [[Ama District, Aichi]]. Throughout her life, she was attached to [[Production Baobab]]; she was attached to [[Aoni Production]] at the time of her death. Mizutani was best known for her roles of Sakiko Sakura in ''[[Chibi Maruko-chan]]'', Mihoshi Kuramitsu in ''[[Tenchi Muyo!]]'', Excellen Browning in ''[[Super Robot Wars]]'', Sora Takenouchi in ''[[Digimon Adventure]]'', Leina Stol in ''[[Machine Robo: Revenge of Cronos]]'', Sarah Zabiarov and Cheimin Noa in ''[[Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam]]'' and Pinoko in ''[[Black Jack (manga)|Black Jack]]''. Mizutani was the official Japanese voice actress for [[Minnie Mouse]] from 1991 until her death;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.mynavi.jp/news/2016/05/19/429/|script-title=ja:\u58f0\u512a\u30fb\u6c34\u8c37\u512a\u5b50\u3055\u3093\u304c\u4e73\u304c\u3093\u3067\u6b7b\u53bb\u3001\u4ee3\u8868\u4f5c\u306f\u300e\u3061\u3073\u307e\u308b\u5b50\u3061\u3083\u3093\u300f|language=Japanese|publisher=Mynavi|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=May 21, 2016}}</ref> she also voiced her in the ''[[Kingdom Hearts]]'' franchise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/popculturenow/2016/05/19/original-voice-actress-for-digimons-sora-yuko-mizutani-dies-at-5/|last=Lovett|first=Jamie|title=Original Voice Actress For Digimon's Sora, Yuko Mizutani, Dies At 51|language=English|work=comicbook.com|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=May 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<!-- ==Sakiko==\nShe voiced the role of Maruko's older sister in ''[[Chibi Maruko-chan]]'' in 1990, alongside co-stars [[Tarako]] (Momoko \"Maruko\" Sakura), [[Kei Tomiyama]] (Tomozo), [[Y\u016bsaku Yara]] (Hiroshi), [[Teiy\u016b Ichiry\u016bsai]] (Sumire), Y\u016bko Sasaki (Kotake), [[Naoko Watanabe (voice actress)|Naoko Watanabe]] (Tamae Honami), [[Masami Kikuchi]] (Kazuhiko Hanawa), [[Nobuo Tobita]] (Sueo Maruo) and [[Keiko Yamamoto]] (Shouta Yamada). In 1995, they reprised their roles until their deaths. Mizutani succumbed to [[Breast cancer]] in 2016, Tomiyama from [[Pancreatic cancer]] in 1995 before his role was taken over by [[Takeshi Aono]] who went on medical leave due to [[Aortic dissection]] in 2010 before [[Bin Shimada]] took over as her grandpa before Aono succumbed to brain hemorrhage in 2012.\n\n==Mihoshi==\nMizutani was cast in 1995 as ''[[Tenchi Muyo!]]'''s character [[List of Tenchi Muyo! characters|Mihoshi Kuramitsu]], a Galaxy Police detective, alongside co-stars [[Masaki Kajishima]] (Tenchi Masaki), [[Ai Orikasa]] (Ryoko), [[Yumi Takada]] (Ayeka Jurai), [[Chisa Yokoyama]] (Sasami Jurai), [[Etsuko Kozakura]] (Ryo-Ohki), [[Yuko Kobayashi]] (Washu Hakubi) and [[Yuri Amano]] (Kiyone Makibi), when it came to 1997 until 2014, she reprised her role as well, the sole exception being the [[Super Famicom]] from 1995. Her role was given to [[Michie Tomizawa]] in ''Ryo-Ohki 4''.\n\n==Sora Takenouchi==\n\n{{Empty section|date=February 2020}}\n\n==Pinoko==\nOn December 21, 1993, she voiced Pinoko, Black Jack's loyal assistant/kind of adopted daughter, who was actually a Teratogenous Cystoma (a growth more commonly known as a teratoma) in [[Osamu Tezuka]]'s ''[[Black Jack (manga)|Black Jack (OVA)]]'' alongside the [[Black Jack (manga character)|title character]]'s [[Voice acting in Japan|voice actor]] [[Akio \u014ctsuka]]. In 2004, they reprised their roles in a TV series until 2011. -->\n\n==Personal life==\nIn November 1994, she married Mizuho Nishikubo. They were married until her death.\n\n==Death==\nOn May 17, 2016, Mizutani died as a result of breast cancer. She was 51 years old at the time of her death.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20160519-00000328-oric-ent|script-title=ja:\u58f0\u512a\u30fb\u6c34\u8c37\u512a\u5b50\u3055\u3093\u3001\u4e73\u304c\u3093\u3067\u6b7b\u53bb\u3000\u300e\u3061\u3073\u307e\u308b\u5b50\u3061\u3083\u3093\u300f\u304a\u59c9\u3061\u3083\u3093\u306a\u3069|language=Japanese|work=Yahoo! News|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=May 19, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160519062015/http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20160519-00000328-oric-ent|archivedate=May 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Successors==\n+ marks the time before Mizutani's death\n*[[Michie Tomizawa]]+ ''[[Tenchi Muyo! Ryo-Ohki]]'' (Mihoshi Kuramitsu)\n*[[Machiko Toyoshima]] ''[[Chibi Maruko-chan]]'' (Sakiko Sakura)\n\n==Filmography==\n===Anime television===\n*''[[Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam]]'' (1985-1986) \u2013 [[Sarah Zabiarov]] and Cheimin Noa\n*''[[Dirty Pair]]'' (1985) \u2013 Security Guard, Creamy Girl\n*''[[Machine Robo: Revenge of Cronos]]'' (1986-1987) \u2013 Leina St\u014dl\n*''[[Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ]]'' (1986-1987) \u2013 Milly Childer\n*''[[Zillion (anime)|Zillion]]'' (1987-1987) \u2013 Apple\n*''[[City Hunter#Anime|City Hunter]]'' (1987-1988) \u2013 Yoshimi Iwai\n*''[[Esper Mami]]'' (1987-1989) \u2013 Midori\n*''[[Legend of He