ay the 13th Part VIII: Jason Takes Manhattan]]'' \u2013 Rennie Wickham ([[Jensen Daggett]])\n*''[[The Golden Child]]'' \u2013 Kee Nang ([[Charlotte Lewis]])\n*''[[Highlander III: The Sorcerer]]'' \u2013 Dr. Alexandra Johnson/Sarah Barrington ([[Deborah Kara Unger]])\n*''[[Hollow Man]]'' \u2013 Sarah Kennedy ([[Kim Dickens]])\n*''[[Home Alone]]'' \u2013 Heather McCallister ([[Kristin Minter]])\n*''[[Home Alone 2: Lost in New York]]'' \u2013 Tracy McCallister ([[Senta Moses]])\n*''[[Iron Eagle]]'' \u2013 Amy (Kathy Wagner)\n*''[[Jumanji]]'' \u2013 Judy Shepherd ([[Kirsten Dunst]])\n*''[[King Kong (1976 film)|King Kong]]'' \u2013 Dwan ([[Jessica Lange]])\n*''[[Kiss of Death (1995 film)|Kiss of Death]]'' \u2013 Rosie Kilmartin ([[Kathryn Erbe]])\n*''[[Knock Off (film)|Knock Off]]'' \u2013 Karen Lee ([[Lela Rochon]])\n*''[[Last Action Hero]]'' \u2013 Whitney Slater/Meredith Caprice ([[Bridgette Wilson]])\n*''[[The Last Boy Scout]]'' \u2013 Cory ([[Halle Berry]])\n*''[[A Nightmare on Elm Street]]'' \u2013 Tina Gray ([[Amanda Wyss]])\n*''[[NYPD Blue]]'' \u2013 Robin Wirkus ([[Debrah Farentino]])\n*''[[Pale Rider]]'' \u2013 Megan Wheeler ([[Sydney Penny]])\n*''[[The Pink Panther (1963 film)|The Pink Panther]]'' \u2013 Princess Dala ([[Gale Garnett]])\n*''[[Poison Ivy: The New Seduction]]'' \u2013 Violet ([[Jaime Pressly]])\n*''[[Practical Magic]]'' \u2013 Kylie Owens ([[Evan Rachel Wood]])\n*''[[Return of the Living Dead Part II]]'' \u2013 Lucy Wilson ([[Marsha Dietlein]])\n*''[[Romy and Michele's High School Reunion]]'' \u2013 Christie Masters ([[Julia Campbell]])\n*''[[Scooby-Doo 2: Monsters Unleashed]]'' \u2013 Heather Jasper-Howe ([[Alicia Silverstone]])\n*''[[Short Circuit 2]]'' \u2013 Sandy Banatoni ([[Cynthia Gibb]])\n*''[[Sibling Rivalry (film)|Sibling Rivalry]]'' \u2013 Jeanine ([[Jami Gertz]])\n*''[[Single White Female]]'' \u2013 Hedra \"Hedy\" Carlson/Ellen Besch ([[Jennifer Jason Leigh]])<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.star-ch.jp/channel/detail.php?movie_id=2748|title= \u30eb\u30fc\u30e0\u30e1\u30a4\u30c8|accessdate= March 13, 2019|work= Star Channel}}</ref>\n*''[[Sleepers (film)|Sleepers]]'' \u2013 Carol ([[Minnie Driver]])\n*''[[Stargate SG-1]]'' \u2013 Hathor ([[Suanne Braun]])\n*''[[Three Men and a Baby]]'' \u2013 Sally ([[Barbara Budd]])\n*''[[True Lies]]'' \u2013 Dana Tasker ([[Eliza Dushku]])\n*''[[Vampire in Brooklyn]]'' \u2013 Det. Rita Veder ([[Angela Bassett]])\n*''[[Waitress (film)|Waitress]]'' \u2013 Dawn ([[Adrienne Shelly]])<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.foxjapan.com/waitress|title= \u30a6\u30a7\u30a4\u30c8\u30ec\u30b9\uff5e\u304a\u3044\u3057\u3044\u4eba\u751f\u306e\u3064\u304f\u308a\u304b\u305f|accessdate= March 5, 2019|work= Fox Japan}}</ref>\n*''[[Will & Grace]]'' \u2013 Ellen ([[Leigh-Allyn Baker]])\n\n====Animation====\n*''[[Balto (film)|Balto]]'' \u2013 Rosy\n*''[[Disney's House of Mouse]]'' \u2013 [[Minnie Mouse]]\n*''[[Hercules (1997 film)|Hercules]]'' \u2013 [[Terpsichore]]\n*''[[The Mask: Animated Series]]'' \u2013 Peggy Brandt\n*''[[Mickey, Donald, Goofy: The Three Musketeers]]'' \u2013 Minnie Mouse\n*''[[Peanuts]]'' \u2013 [[Pig-Pen]], [[Violet (Peanuts)|Violet Gray]]\n*''[[Tiny Toon Adventures]]'' \u2013 Sweetie Pie\n\n===Drama CDs===\n*''Analyst no Yuutsu series 1: Benchmark ni Koi wo Shite'' \u2013 Chizuru Mizusawa\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.aoni.co.jp/search/mizutani-yuko.html Official agency profile] {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{ann|people|1004}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=0594730}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mizutani, Yuko}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n[[Category:Aoni Production voice actors]]\n[[Category:Deaths from breast cancer]]\n[[Category:Japanese female singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese video game actresses]]\n[[Category:Japanese voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Aichi Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Production Baobab voice actors]]\n[[Category:Voice actresses from Aichi Prefecture]]\n[[Category:20th-century Japanese actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese actresses]]\n[[Category:20th-century Japanese women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese women singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Y\u016bko Mizutani\n| image              = YukoMizutani.jpg\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software  -->\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u6c34\u8c37\u512a\u5b50\n| native_name_lang   = ja\n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name --> \n| birth_date         = {{birth date|1964|11|04}}\n| birth_place        = [[Ama District, Aichi]], Japan\n| death_date         = {{Death date and age|2016|05|17|1964|11|04}}\n| death_place        = [[Tokyo]], Japan\n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n*Actress\n*[[Voice acting in Japan|voice actress]]\n*narrator\n*singer\n}}\n| years_active       = 1985&ndash;2016\n| agent              = [[Aoni Production]]\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Mizuho Nishikubo|November 1994|May 17, 2016}}\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Y\u016bko Mizutani'''|\u6c34\u8c37 \u512a\u5b50|Mizutani Y\u016bko|November 4, 1964 \u2013 May 17, 2016}} was a Japanese actress, [[Voice acting in Japan|voice actress]], narrator and singer from [[Ama District, Aichi]].\n\n==Career==\nThroughout her life, she was attached to [[Production Baobab]]; she was attached to [[Aoni Production]] at the time of her death. Mizutani was best known for her roles of Sakiko Sakura in ''[[Chibi Maruko-chan]]'', Mihoshi Kuramitsu in ''[[Tenchi Muyo!]]'', Excellen Browning in ''[[Super Robot Wars]]'', Sora Takenouchi in ''[[Digimon Adventure]]'', Leina Stol in ''[[Machine Robo: Revenge of Cronos]]'', Sarah Zabiarov and Cheimin Noa in ''[[Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam]]'' and Pinoko in ''[[Black Jack (manga)|Black Jack]]''. Mizutani was the official Japanese voice actress for [[Minnie Mouse]] from 1991 until her death;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.mynavi.jp/news/2016/05/19/429/|script-title=ja:\u58f0\u512a\u30fb\u6c34\u8c37\u512a\u5b50\u3055\u3093\u304c\u4e73\u304c\u3093\u3067\u6b7b\u53bb\u3001\u4ee3\u8868\u4f5c\u306f\u300e\u3061\u3073\u307e\u308b\u5b50\u3061\u3083\u3093\u300f|language=Japanese|publisher=Mynavi|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=May 21, 2016}}</ref> she also voiced her in the ''[[Kingdom Hearts]]'' franchise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/popculturenow/2016/05/19/original-voice-actress-for-digimons-sora-yuko-mizutani-dies-at-5/|last=Lovett|first=Jamie|title=Original Voice Actress For Digimon's Sora, Yuko Mizutani, Dies At 51|language=English|work=comicbook.com|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=May 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Sakiko==\nShe voiced the role of Maruko's older sister in ''[[Chibi Maruko-chan]]'' in 1990, alongside co-stars [[Tarako]] (Momoko \"Maruko\" Sakura), [[Kei Tomiyama]] (Tomozo), [[Y\u016bsaku Yara]] (Hiroshi), [[Teiy\u016b Ichiry\u016bsai]] (Sumire), Y\u016bko Sasaki (Kotake), [[Naoko Watanabe (voice actress)|Naoko Watanabe]] (Tamae Honami), [[Masami Kikuchi]] (Kazuhiko Hanawa), [[Nobuo Tobita]] (Sueo Maruo) and [[Keiko Yamamoto]] (Shouta Yamada). In 1995, they reprised their roles until their deaths. Mizutani succumbed to [[Breast cancer]] in 2016, Tomiyama from [[Pancreatic cancer]] in 1995 before his role was taken over by [[Takeshi Aono]] who went on medical leave due to [[Aortic dissection]] in 2010 before [[Bin Shimada]] took over as her grandpa before Aono succumbed to brain hemorrhage in 2012.\n\n==Mihoshi==\nMizutani was cast in 1995 as ''[[Tenchi Muyo!]]'''s character [[List of Tenchi Muyo! characters|Mihoshi Kuramitsu]], a Galaxy Police detective, alongside co-stars [[Masaki Kajishima]] (Tenchi Masaki), [[Ai Orikasa]] (Ryoko), [[Yumi Takada]] (Ayeka Jurai), [[Chisa Yokoyama]] (Sasami Jurai), [[Etsuko Kozakura]] (Ryo-Ohki), [[Yuko Kobayashi]] (Washu Hakubi) and [[Yuri Amano]] (Kiyone Makibi), when it came to 1997 until 2014, she reprised her role as well, the sole exception being the [[Super Famicom]] from 1995. Her role was given to [[Michie Tomizawa]] in ''Ryo-Ohki 4''.\n\n==Sora Takenouchi==\n\n{{Empty section|date=February 2020}}\n\n==Pinoko==\nOn December 21, 1993, she voiced Pinoko, Black Jack's loyal assistant/kind of adopted daughter, who was actually a Teratogenous Cystoma (a growth more commonly known as a teratoma) in [[Osamu Tezuka]]'s ''[[Black Jack (manga)|Black Jack (OVA)]]'' alongside the [[Black Jack (manga character)|title character]]'s [[Voice acting in Japan|voice actor]] [[Akio \u014ctsuka]]. In 2004, they reprised their roles in a TV series until 2011.\n\n==Personal life==\nIn November 1994, she married Mizuho Nishikubo.  They were married until her death.\n\n==Death==\nOn May 17, 2016, Mizutani died as a result of breast cancer. She was 51 years old at the time of her death.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20160519-00000328-oric-ent|script-title=ja:\u58f0\u512a\u30fb\u6c34\u8c37\u512a\u5b50\u3055\u3093\u3001\u4e73\u304c\u3093\u3067\u6b7b\u53bb\u3000\u300e\u3061\u3073\u307e\u308b\u5b50\u3061\u3083\u3093\u300f\u304a\u59c9\u3061\u3083\u3093\u306a\u3069|language=Japanese|work=Yahoo! News|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=May 19, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160519062015/http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20160519-00000328-oric-ent|archivedate=May 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Successors==\n+ marks the time before Mizutani's death\n*[[Michie Tomizawa]]+ ''[[Tenchi Muyo! Ryo-Ohki]]'' (Mihoshi Kuramitsu)\n*[[Machiko Toyoshima]] ''[[Chibi Maruko-chan]]'' (Sakiko Sakura)\n\n==Filmography==\n===Anime television===\n*''[[Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam]]'' (1985-1986) \u2013 [[Sarah Zabiarov]] and Cheimin Noa\n*''[[Dirty Pair]]'' (1985) \u2013 Security Guard, Creamy Girl\n*''[[Machine Robo: Revenge of Cronos]]'' (1986-1987) \u2013 Leina St\u014dl\n*''[[Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ]]'' (1986-1987) \u2013 Milly Childer\n*''[[Zillion (anime)|Zillion]]'' (1987-1987) \